ANALYSIS REQUEST

The dataset is a seurat object from a recent study. It’s a merged object with three samples “AD_sham”, “AD_7d”, and “AD_28d”.

Question 1

  1. Generate a general set of descriptive figures.
  2. Generate a UMAP split by sample.
  3. Generate a stacked barplot on the cluster proportions per sample,
  4. Generate heatmap of average cluster expression of Top5 DEGs for each cluster.

Question 2

  1. Run WGCNA to extract pertinent modules.
  2. Show the ME scores as features on the UMAP plot split by sample.
  3. Generate pathway enrichment using a package of your choice.
  4. Calculate enrichment scores by cluster, as well as WGCNA modules for KEGG, GO_BP, and mSigDB.

Figure 7: Heatmap of average expression of Top 5 DEGs per sample 

new_colnames= c("cluster","gene","avg_log2FC","pct.1","pct.2",
             "pct.diff","p_val","p_val_adj")


AD_Marker <- FindAllMarkers(seurat_obj, 
                             logfc.threshold = 0.25, 
                             min.pct = 0.05, 
                             only.pos = TRUE)
AD_Marker <- data.table(AD_Marker)

AD_Marker=AD_Marker %>% mutate(pct.diff = pct.1 - pct.2) %>%
  select(all_of(new_colnames)) %>%
  group_by(cluster) %>%
  dplyr::filter(avg_log2FC >= 0.5)
load("AD_Marker.RData")
seurat_obj@misc$marker <- AD_Marker     # Store markers into Seurat object

colGEX = c("grey85", brewer.pal(7, "BuPu"))      # color for gene expression
colCcy = c("black", "blue", "darkorange")  
reorderCluster=c("8","0","5","7","4","6","1","3","2")


# Reorder the cluster factor levels
AD_Marker <- AD_Marker %>%
  mutate(cluster = factor(cluster, levels = reorderCluster))

# Order the dataframe by cluster and descending avg_log2FC
AD_Marker <- AD_Marker %>%
  arrange(cluster, desc(avg_log2FC))

# Select top 5 genes per cluster
topGene <- AD_Marker %>%
  filter(cluster %in% reorderCluster) %>%
  group_by(cluster) %>%
  slice_max(order_by = avg_log2FC, n = 5) %>%
  pull(gene) %>%
  unique()

p0=DoHeatmap(seurat_obj, features = topGene, group.colors =colCls )+ labs(title = "Average cluster expression of Top 5 DEGs") + plotTheme

p1 <- DotPlot(seurat_obj, group.by = "seurat_clusters", features =  topGene) + 
  coord_flip() + scale_color_gradientn(colors = colGEX) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = -45, hjust = 0))


p2 <- VlnPlot(seurat_obj, group.by = "seurat_clusters", fill.by = "ident", cols = colCls, features = topGene, stack = TRUE, flip = TRUE)

Question 2

Run WGCNA to extract pertinent modules.

seurat_obj <- SetupForWGCNA(
  seurat_obj,
  gene_select = "fraction", # the gene selection approach
  fraction = 0.05, # fraction of cells that a gene needs to be expressed in order to be included
  wgcna_name = "AD_pro" # the name of the hdWGCNA experiment
)

# construct metacells  in each group
seurat_obj <- MetacellsByGroups(
  seurat_obj = seurat_obj,
  group.by = c("seurat_clusters", "orig.ident"), 
  reduction = 'umap', 
  k = 25, # nearest-neighbors parameter
  max_shared = 10, # maximum number of shared cells between two metacells
  ident.group = 'seurat_clusters' # set the Idents of the metacell seurat object
)

# normalize metacell expression matrix:
seurat_obj <- NormalizeMetacells(seurat_obj)


seurat_obj <- SetDatExpr(
  seurat_obj,
  group_name = reorderCluster, 
  group.by='seurat_clusters', 
  assay = 'SCT', # using SCT assay
  slot = 'data' # using normalized data
)


# Test different soft powers:
seurat_obj <- TestSoftPowers(
  seurat_obj,
  networkType = 'signed' # you can also use "unsigned" or "signed hybrid"
)

# plot the results:
plot_list <- PlotSoftPowers(seurat_obj)

# assemble with patchwork
wrap_plots(plot_list, ncol=2)

power_table <- GetPowerTable(seurat_obj)
head(power_table, 10)

# construct co-expression network:
seurat_obj <- ConstructNetwork(
  seurat_obj,
  tom_name = 'AD_pro_CLUST_all' # name of the topoligical overlap matrix written to disk
)


PlotDendrogram(seurat_obj, main='AD hdWGCNA Dendrogram')
TOM <- GetTOM(seurat_obj)

# need to run ScaleData first or else harmony throws an error:

seurat_obj <- ScaleData(seurat_obj, features=VariableFeatures(seurat_obj))

# compute all MEs in the full single-cell dataset
seurat_obj <- ModuleEigengenes(
  seurat_obj,
  group.by.vars="orig.ident")

# harmonized module eigengenes:
hMEs <- GetMEs(seurat_obj)

# module eigengenes:
MEs <- GetMEs(seurat_obj, harmonized=FALSE)

# compute eigengene-based connectivity (kME):
seurat_obj <- ModuleConnectivity(
  seurat_obj,
  group.by = 'seurat_clusters', group_name = reorderCluster
)


# rename the modules

# get modules and TOM from the seurat obj
modules <- GetModules(seurat_obj) %>% 
  subset(module != 'grey') %>% 
  mutate(module = droplevels(module))
mods <- levels(modules$module)
TOM <- GetTOM(seurat_obj)

# get module colors for plotting 
mod_colors <- dplyr::select(modules, c(module, color)) %>% distinct()
mod_cp <- mod_colors$color; names(mod_cp) <- as.character(mod_colors$module)

# load the GO Biological Pathways file (donwloaded from EnrichR website)
pathways <- fgsea::gmtPathways('BP_Gene.txt')

# remove GO Term ID for simplicity:
names(pathways) <- stringr::str_replace(names(pathways), " \\s*\\([^\\)]+\\)", "")


# selected pathway 
cur_pathway <- 'Central Nervous System Development'

# get genes in this pathway 
cur_genes <- pathways[[cur_pathway]]


mouse_human_genes <- read.csv("http://www.informatics.jax.org/downloads/reports/HOM_MouseHumanSequence.rpt",sep="\t")
                              
    # separate human and mouse 
    mouse <- split.data.frame(mouse_human_genes,mouse_human_genes$Common.Organism.Name)[[2]]
    human <- split.data.frame(mouse_human_genes,mouse_human_genes$Common.Organism.Name)[[1]]
    
    # remove some columns
    mouse <- mouse[,c(1,4)]
    human <- human[,c(1,4)]
    
    # merge the 2 dataset  (note that the human list is longer than the mouse one)
    mh_data <- merge.data.frame(mouse,human,by = "DB.Class.Key",all.y = TRUE) 
    
    modules= merge(modules,mh_data, by.x="gene_name", by.y="Symbol.x" )
    
    
cur_genes <- cur_genes[cur_genes %in% modules$Symbol.y]
cur_genes= mh_data[mh_data$Symbol.y %in% cur_genes, 2]
# subset the TOM 
cur_TOM <- TOM[cur_genes,cur_genes] 


# set up the graph object with igraph & tidygraph
graph <- cur_TOM %>% 
  igraph::graph_from_adjacency_matrix(mode='undirected', weighted=TRUE) %>% 
  tidygraph::as_tbl_graph(directed=FALSE) %>% 
  tidygraph::activate(nodes) 

# add the module name to the graph:
V(graph)$module <- modules[ modules$gene_name %in% V(graph)$name,'module']

# make the plot with gggraph
pp <- ggraph(graph) + 
  geom_edge_link(aes(alpha=weight), color='grey') + 
  geom_node_point(aes(color=module)) +
  geom_node_label(aes(label=name), repel=TRUE, max.overlaps=Inf, fontface='italic') +
  scale_colour_manual(values=mod_cp)  
pp

gsva_result <- analyse_sc_clusters(seurat_obj, verbose = TRUE)

pathway_expression <- pathways(gsva_result)

# simplify the column names by removing the default dataset identifier
colnames(pathway_expression) <- gsub("\\.Seurat", "", colnames(pathway_expression))

pathway_expression[1:3,]


# find the maximum differently expressed pathway
max_difference <- do.call(rbind, apply(pathway_expression, 1, function(row) {
  values <- as.numeric(row[2:length(row)])
  return(data.frame(name = row[1], min = min(values), max = max(values)))
}))

max_difference$diff <- max_difference$max - max_difference$min

# sort based on the difference
max_difference <- max_difference[order(max_difference$diff, decreasing = T), ]

head(max_difference)
